## 🐞 Debugging Workflow  
I built an enhanced debugging setup where errors and data structures are displayed with Rich formatting. 
I chose to build this because debugging is often tedious, and Rich makes errors and data structures much easier to read. 
The system works by replacing Python’s default traceback handler and `print` function. Exceptions are displayed with color-coded tracebacks, 
and objects are pretty-printed with indentation and styling. From this project, I learned that Rich can save time during debugging 
by making errors and data instantly readable, which improves developer productivity and reduces cognitive load.  

---

## 🌟 Overall Insight  
Across these tasks, I discovered that Rich is not just about adding color — it’s about clarity, structure, and interactivity. 
It can be applied in monitoring, task management, debugging, and even web dashboards, making it a versatile tool for developers. 
These projects helped me understand how Rich can be leveraged to build professional, interactive console applications and lightweight dashboards.  
